3–1581":"1503–1581","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1505–1585":"1505–1585","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1599":"1599","1585":"1585","1581":"1581","about 1585":"omkring 1585","1505":"1505","Braunton, Devon, England":"Braunton, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1505–about 1585":"1505–circa 1585","1503–1581":"1503–1581","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1505–1585":"1505–1585","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1599":"1599","1585":"1585","1581":"1581","about 1585":"circa 1585","1505":"1505","Braunton, Devon, England":"Braunton, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1505–about 1585":"1505–about 1585","1503–1581":"1503–1581","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1505–1585":"1505–1585","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1599":"1599","1585":"1585","1581":"1581","about 1585":"about 1585","1505":"1505","Braunton, Devon, England":"Braunton, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Perrin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French and English: from the Old French and Middle English personal name <i>Perrin</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perine  ,   Perrine  , and   Prine  .","History: Henri Perrin from Louargat in Côtes-d'Armor, Brittany (France), married Jeanne Merrin in Montreal, QC, in 1661. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its variants or altered forms <i>Perrine</i> and <i>Pareyn</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America. One of the Huguenot ancestors was Daniel Perrin (1642–1719), nicknamed <i>The Huguenot</i>, who arrived in New York in 1665, aboard the <i>Philip</i>, and settled first in NJ and later on Staten Island. Among his descendants the surname is common in the altered forms <i>Perrine</i>, <i>Perine</i> and <i>Prine</i>. The Staten Island community of Huguenot is named after Daniel Perrin and other Huguenots who settled in the area during the late 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Prine","meanings":["Americanized form of French   Perrin  .","In some cases also an Americanized form of Dutch   Pruyn   or perhaps of some other similar (like-sounding) surname.","History: The surname <i>Prine</i> is established among the descendants of the Huguenot immigrant Daniel Perrin (1642–1719); see   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Pierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."]},{"name":"Perren","meanings":["French and English (of French Huguenot origin): variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Parren","meanings":["English: variant of   Perrin  ."]},{"name":"Perrine","meanings":["French: from the feminine form of   Perrin   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","English: variant of   Perrin  . This surname is now rare in Britain and Ireland.","History: The surname <i>Perrine</i> of French origin (see 1 above) is listed along with its original form   Perrin   in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Parran","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Monique.","Altered form of French   Perrin  . This surname was brought to England by the Huguenots, but has died out there.","In some cases possibly also southern French: topographic name from Occitan <i>parran</i> ‘small garden behind a house’. This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Perrins","meanings":["English (West Midlands): variant of   Perrin  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Perrin was born in 1505, in Georgeham, Devon, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mary Selwoode Perrin. He died about 1585, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1505–about 1585":"1505–umbes 1585","1503–1581":"1503–1581","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1505–1585":"1505–1585","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1599":"1599","1585":"1585","1581":"1581","about 1585":"umbes 1585","1505":"1505","Braunton, Devon, England":"Braunton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1505–about 1585":"1505–noin 1585","1503–1581":"1503–1581","1535–1599":"1535–1599","1505–1585":"1505–1585","1503":"1503","1535":"1535","1599":"1599","1585":"1585","1581":"1581","about 1585":"noin 1585","1505":"1505","Braunton, Devon, England":"Braunton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Georgeham, Devonshire, England":"Georgeham, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Eng